#Step 1: Define a Function to Load Images
#Define a function to load images from the dataset. 
#This function will read images from the directories 
#and convert them into a format suitable for your model.
def load_images_from_folder(folder, max_images=10):
    images = []
    labels = []
    
    for label in os.listdir(folder):
        label_folder = os.path.join(folder, label)
        if not os.path.isdir(label_folder):
            continue

        image_count = 0
        for filename in os.listdir(label_folder):
            img_path = os.path.join(label_folder, filename)
            try:
                img = Image.open(img_path).convert('RGB')
                images.append(np.array(img))
                labels.append(label)
                image_count += 1
                if image_count >= max_images:
                    break
            except:
                print(f"Failed to load image at {img_path}")
    return np.array(images), np.array(labels)

#Implement Early Stopping and Model Checkpoint
#Early stopping will halt the training 
#when the validation loss stops improving, 
#preventing overfitting. 
#Model checkpoint saves the best model during training.
from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping, ModelCheckpoint

# Early stopping callback
early_stopping = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=5)

# Model checkpoint callback
model_checkpoint = ModelCheckpoint(
    'best_model.h5', 
    monitor='val_loss', 
    save_best_only=True)

# Train the model with data augmentation
history = model.fit(datagen.flow(X_train, y_train_encoded, batch_size=32),
                    epochs=50,  # Increase epochs
                    validation_data=(X_test, y_test_encoded),
                    callbacks=[early_stopping, model_checkpoint])

# this code assessed my camera and tried to reconise my face 
# however I had to stop it and i did not include my photograph and video to the mode
# this was only a example i tried on my own and the model worked 

import cv2
import numpy as np
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.models import load_model
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import img_to_array

# Load your trained model
model = load_model('/Users/shiveshrajsahu/Desktop/Cs767/final project/best_model.h5')

# Initialize webcam
cap = cv2.VideoCapture(0)

while True:
    # Capture frame-by-frame
    ret, frame = cap.read()
    if not ret:
        break

    # Convert the captured frame to RGB
    color_frame = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)

    # Resize the frame to your model's expected input size
    resized_frame = cv2.resize(color_frame, (224, 224))

    # Preprocess the frame
    resized_frame = img_to_array(resized_frame)
    resized_frame = np.expand_dims(resized_frame, axis=0)
    resized_frame = resized_frame / 255.0

    # Predict the class
    prediction = model.predict(resized_frame)
    class_index = np.argmax(prediction, axis=1)

    # You may want to map class_index to actual label names
    label = f'Class: {class_index}'

    # Display the resulting frame with label
    cv2.putText(frame, label, (10, 30), cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX, 1, (0, 255, 0), 2)
    cv2.imshow('Real-Time Face Recognition', frame)

    # Break the loop with 'q'
    if cv2.waitKey(1) & 0xFF == ord('q'):
        break

# When everything is done, release the capture
cap.release()
cv2.destroyAllWindows()
